You'll configure and run CodeBuild for a project, including defining build specifications and integrating with other AWS services.

Before creation of codebuild project make role with any name here i took
code-build-service-role , this role is for codebuild service so select that also and give permission for AmazonSSMFullAccess then you have to create parameter in systems manager with secureString type for docker user , docker password and url as docker.io.

Then create project for codeBuild give name set repo url , authenticate with github with main branch then select ubuntu as operating system and runtime as standard and then here you have to select that role which you created and for buildspec use this

version: 0.2

env:
  parameter-store:
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME: docker-hub-username
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_URL: docker-url
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD: docker-password

phases:
  install:
    runtime-versions:
      python: 3.11

  pre_build:
    commands:
      - echo "Logging in to Docker Hub..."
      - echo $DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD | docker login -u $DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME --password-stdin
      - pip install -r 11-python-project/requirements.txt

  build:
    commands:
      - cd 11-python-project
      - echo "Building Docker image..."
      - docker build -t $DOCKER_REGISTRY_URL/$DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME/python-project:latest .

  post_build:
    commands:
      - echo "Pushing Docker image..."
      - docker push $DOCKER_REGISTRY_URL/$DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME/python-project:latest


Then just create this project then start build and it will be successfull. This just manual test to see if build work or not, now we will create a code pipeline to automate this CI.

create pipeline then click on Build custom pipeline give any pipeline name and then next , then in source stage select GitHub (via OAuth app) 
and connect git then select your repo and main branch then next and then in build step select Other build providers and select aws code build and select your build and then next and skip test stage and skip deploy stage (deployment is part of other project) then create pipeline.

And now when you change your code  and commit then pipeline will be triggered.
 
